<title>POLAND: Vistula to lay off 206 employees.</title>
<headline>Vistula to lay off 206 employees.</headline>
<dateline>WARSAW 1997-01-22</dateline>
<text>
<p>Polish garment maker Vistula SA plans to lay off 206 employees at its plant in Przeworsk, southern Poland, as the factory moves to a one-shift system, the company said in a statement on Wednesday.</p>
<p>The statement said the conditions of the dismissals had to be agreed upon with the plant's trade unions.</p>
<p>Last Saturday the plant's director told the daily Parkiet that the lay-offs could prove necessary as the factory, which currently employs 500, shifts production to domestic from foreign markets.</p>
<p>-- Warsaw Newsroom +48 22 653 9700</p>
